What is a server? What is the difference between client and a server?

A server is a computer or system that provides data, services, or resources to other computers over a network.
For example, when you open a website, a server sends the webpage data to your device.

A client is a device or application that requests services or data from a server.

Examples:

Web browser (Chrome, Safari)
Mobile apps
Your laptop or phone

Interview:
A server is a system that provides data or services, while a client is a device or application that requests and consumes those services.

Difference Between Client and Server

Feature	                  Client	              Server
Role	                    Requests data	        Provides data
Example	                  Browser, mobile app	  Web server, database server
Initiates communication	  Yes	                  No (responds to requests)
Function	                Displays/uses data	  Stores/processes data
